R1: It appears the robot is facing the corner of a room without any furniture or place to sit. You would mop/vacuum into the corner, perhaps even place things, but you wouldn't eat or talk facing a corner like that. Your back is to the main seating area and it may intimidate if you talk to someone in a corner like that.
R2: You would probably take food to the majority of people (behind you) but you could also be taking it away. A conversation seems inappropriate as most people are behind you.
R3: You're away from everyone so may do mopping etc. but almost all others would seem unusual or out of character.
R4: You're in the middle of a group so talking is expected, maybe even sharing food/drinks if careful. Chores or carrying big items would be inconvenient and possibly dangerous considering the closeness of the couch.
R5: Avoiding the danger/challenge of stairs, it would be fine to move around this space. You're starting far enough away from the only person in the space so they would have time to move.
R6: There's nowhere to take objects/food in that corner (assuming the robot doesn't go through the door) so it would be pointless. You can probably vacuum as people are a distance away.
R7: You're walking at a wall so where are the food/drinks going? They need to go to the kitchen or the people. It'd be too noisy to vacuum here as people are taking. This should have been an answer earlier for one photo!
R8: One person could easily move away if you started making noise. There's nowhere to take food, drink or objects so it would seem unusual behaviour.
R9: The two people aren't talking so it's fine to clean. You can take food in/out of the room and move objects in a large space.
R10: There's one man who can be made aware of your presence with audio stimulus making tasks easy to complete.
R11: Two people close together may want drink/food but be careful. Cleaning and heavy lifting would be inconvenient to the two people.
R12: The couple appear to be watching TV so a vacuum would be too noisy. Food/drink may be appropriate if people want them.
R13: Everyone is away from you which makes cleaning acceptable but conversations/service impossible.
R14: Too close to the wall to do most things and too close to the people to vacuum.
R15: There are people close enough to serve or talk to but they're too close for vacuuming (noise) or lifting (danger).
R16: Too many people to clean/lift heavy things as they will have an uncomfortable experience. Carrying food etc. seems appropriate as there are people who may want them.
R17: There's one man too close to carry big things but you may want to offer him food/drink.
R18: Safe to do most things because the people are far enough away to see/hear and react if they need to.
R19: Conversation and service are the things you'd expect in these circumstances. Cleaning and carrying would be inconvenient for others.
R20: You're carrying and cleaning out of the room (to the kitchen?) but cannot talk to people who are too far away.
